		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Process theology</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Process theology</b> is a school of thought influenced by the metaphysical <a href="/wiki/Process_philosophy" title="Process philosophy">process philosophy</a> of <a href="/wiki/Alfred_North_Whitehead" title="Alfred North Whitehead">Alfred North Whitehead</a> (1861–1947). While there are process theologies that are similar, but unrelated to the work of Whitehead (such as <a href="/wiki/Pierre_Teilhard_de_Chardin" title="Pierre Teilhard de Chardin">Pierre Teilhard de Chardin</a>) the term is generally applied to the Whiteheadian school. Process theology is unrelated to the <a href="/wiki/Process_Church" title="Process Church" class="mw-redirect">Process Church</a>.</p>
